  "prompt": "How do you know that the girl sitting next to you wants you to talk to her?",
  "response": "Determining if someone wants to engage in conversation can involve several verbal and non-verbal cues. Here are a few signs that might indicate the girl next to you is open to talking:\n\n1. **Eye Contact**: If she frequently makes eye contact with you, especially if she smiles or looks away shyly, it\u2019s a good sign she\u2019s interested.\n\n2. **Body Language**: Open body language, such as facing you, leaning slightly in your direction, or uncrossed arms, can indicate she\u2019s receptive to conversation.\n\n3. **Proximity**: If she\u2019s sitting close to you or has oriented herself towards you, that can suggest she\u2019s comfortable and open to chatting.\n\n4. **Engagement with Surroundings**: If she looks around but returns her gaze to you, or if she seems to be waiting for something (like a question or comment from you), she may be inviting conversation.\n\n5. **Previous Interactions**: If you\u2019ve interacted before and there was a positive exchange, she may be more likely to want to talk again.\n\n6. **Attempts to Start Conversation**: If she initiates small talk or asks questions, that\u2019s a pretty clear indication she wants to engage.\n\nIf you feel comfortable, you can start with a simple greeting or comment about your shared environment to break the ice.",
